9:
Hmm. So you had some mettle after
all. How vexing.
14:
There's no one left to protect you.
Hand over Barusu to us.
18:
I see... If that's the case, then how
about a little bit of... this?
21:
O all-devouring Darkness...
O dark Labyrinth hidden from the
sun's radiance...
Show me what truly lurks within!
25: What is this place? Where am I?
28:
Subaru! Are you okay? Whatever
you do, don't leave my side!
32:
Subaru? Wake up, Subaru! What's
going on?
41:
Sister... I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.
45:
Rem, please.
Don't leave me alone...
67: Heh... This much, even I can do!
74:
You claim to be able to send me
back to my world, but...
78:
I could never go along with
someone like you. Not when you
hurt my friends!
91:
Are you okay, Mili? I kicked the crap
out of that guy, so you don't have to
worry anymore!
95:
I intended to rescue you, but it
seems I was the one who was
rescued—yet again.
100:
Why is it... that nothing ever goes
according to plan? All these damn
interruptions...
102:
Fools, the lot of you! Though the
blame for this failure lies on me as
well...
111:
(Crap... Did our only chance of
getting back home disappear with
that guy? I was so focused on taking
him out, I completely forgot...)
117:
Thanks to you, we've escaped this
predicament unscathed. How can
we ever thank you?
121:
There's no need—I'm sure you would
have done the same for us.
124:
Now that we've saved Subaru, what
do you intend to do next?
132:
Well, since we're not sure what to do,
I figure we might as well stay in
Palpebra! Everyone here's taking
real good care of us, after all!
137:
How can you say something like
that, Barusu? Did the kidnapping
make you lose your senses?
142:
No, that was a serious suggestion! I
mean, we know next to nothing
about this world!
145:
Who knows how long it'll take to find
a way home. We might run out of
money to pay for lodging!
149:
Before that happens, I figured it'd be
best to find some work and make
sure we have clothing and
shelter—using Alk's connections, of
course.
154:
Er, you don't even need to do all
that. We can just ask the Guild for a
favor—I'm sure they'll take care of
you guys!
158:
Are you for real, Alk?! If that's the
case, then staying in Palpebra is
definitely our best bet!
162:
I agree. I think the safest thing to do
would be to establish a foothold
here.
167:
Yes. I'm surprised, Barusu. Your
suggestions are rarely that
worthwhile.
173:
Oh come on, I actually had a good
idea there! I deserve some better
praise than that!
178:
Do we really have the time to be
standing around like this? Everyone
back home is probably worried
about us...
182:
We'll do everything we can to find a
way back to Lugunica! Still... there's
no telling how long it'll take.
185:
Plus, you never know when someone
else like that mage could pop up!
187:
If you consider all of that, getting our
life here set up and stabilized should
probably be our top priority.
190:
I know you're eager to get back
home, but don't worry. We haven't
given up on it!
197:
It's okay. If we work together, I'm
positive we'll find a way back home!
199:
Still, we can't go and do anything
reckless.
201:
If we want to get back in one piece,
we'll need to make sure we take the
time to rest while we're here!
206:
I understand.
I believe in you, Subaru.
210:
You can leave everything to me! I
am and always will be on your side,
Mili!
215:
Well, then. Once you've gotten
settled here, let's speak again.
Please feel free to consult us if you
have any questions!
218:
There likely isn't much we can do for
you, but you have our promise that
we'll do everything in our power to
aid you!
222:
Everything, huh? You know what I'm
in the mood for? Sinking my face
into something nice and fluffy—like
YOU!
233:
Since you've been such a help to us,
we will make sure to repay you in
kind.
237:
I'm sure that you can find a use for
our powers at some point on your
adventures.
242:
Indeed. Always being on the
receiving end is disgraceful. If you
ever need our help, please tell us
immediately.
248:
We'll make sure to do that! You guys
should feel free to do the same, of
course!
253:
You bet! Thanks for all your help, Big
Boss Alk!
